post_text:
Good Morning!

A few parents have emailed me about student drop off and pick up at Atco. Our procedure is not as involved as WES and Assumption. Buses will line up on Cooper Road and parents will drop off/pick-up in the parking lot along side of the school. We plan to have two options forpick up: 1) Drive up and form line along the curb or 2) Park in the designated area and walk up. Circles have been painted for social distancing purposes.

Parents will need to show identification, but not physically sign out. We will call students down similar to how we call buses to ensure social distancing.

Please be patient with us. This is one of those things we need to live through and adjust as we experience it.

Enjoy this beautiful day!
~Dr. Harring

Good Morning Waterford! Just a reminder to those that indicated the need for a Chromebook.

Device Pick-Up Dates are today and tomorrow! These dates are for our remote and hybrid learners that do not have in-person class on the first day of school.

September 2nd (WES)
3rd/4th Grade- 12:30-2:00
5th/6th Grade- 2:00-3:30

September 3rd (WES)
PK-2 - Remote/Hybrid- 12:30-2:00

Our intention is to have a 1:1 for grades 3-6, In addition, the district will provide devices as needed in grade PK-2. However, there is a back order on Chromebooks until November!

Just as we struggled with securing disinfectant wipes technology is challenging to get at this time as well.

post_text:
Our administrative team met yesterday discuss the status of our opening preparations. To date, things are moving along in a timely manner. All buildings are in the final stages of preparation. Teachers will be able to enter the buildings to get classrooms ready on Monday. Class lists have been finalized and mailed. Transportation routes are in process. The mailing will go out late next week.

Our only issue to date is... we could use DISINFECTANT WIPES! If you happen to be in a place where they have them in stock the district would appreciate the donation. Just send them into school with your child. Although we have a supply, they are very difficult to get at this time and we anticipate using them more frequently than previous years.

As always, we appreciate your support during this challenging time.

Stay healthy,
~Dr. Harring üòä

Have you visited the Parent Portal lately and noticed that it still has the 2019-20 data displaying? The new year doesn't switch over officially until the start of the school year but you can still access the upcoming year.

Log in and click on the 3 lines at the top right, then click on My Account. From here you can link students, change your password or change the year displayed. The only thing you will see for this year is your child's Homeroom. Nothing else will be available until the year starts.

post_text:
Now that the dust has settled a bit from our very busy last week of school, I wanted to take a moment to thank everyone for a successful conclusion to our school year. I realize it wasn't easy, even quite challenging at times, but we all pulled together as a community to make the best of it for the children.

In 15 years as an administrator, I usually hear from people when there's a problem, but during this time I had so many parents reach out to show appreciation. Thank you for taking the time to share your thoughts! We all need a pat on the back now and then. Sometimes it's just enough to keep us going in a difficult time.

I will be providing updates about our reopening plans in the weeks to come, but in the meantime enjoy the SUMMER! School is officially out! üòä

~Dr. Harring

I will be providing updates about our reopening plans in the weeks to come, but in the meantime enjoy the SUMMER! School is officially out! üòä

~Dr. Harring

We had our first 6th grade committee meeting Thursday. The district has begun discussions on how to recognize our 6th grade students in a special way.

Our student council officers had a virtual meeting last week with the advisors to ensure the children feel as if they have a voice in the process. Once we get approval that our plan meets the standard of conduct, the district will provide further communication.

If you have a picture you would like us to share from the Friday lawn sign deliveries, we'd be happy to put a post out to capture everyone's moment.

Feel free to email them to me at bharring@wtsd.org. I'd love to see them! I will make sure to get them on our page.

Thank you for your continued patience and support during this time!

Stay safe!
~Dr. Harring

post_text:
At tonight's Board of Education meeting, the Board voted to amend the 2019-2020 School Calendar to reflect the following:

Spring Break will be April 10th and 13th for students.

Teachers will have a In-Service Day on April 13th to discuss the remote learning platform.

School will be in session via remote learning April 14, 15, 16, and 17th.

Instead of an In-Service Day, school will be in session on May 8th.

June 8, 9, 10, 11, and 12th will be early dismissal days.

The school year will conclude on June 12th.

A calendar will be posted on our website and sent via Blackboard tomorrow.

We appreciate the feedback from both parents and staff. The results of the parent survey were 405 to 70 in favor of adjusting the calendar.

Thank you!

The school year will conclude on June 12th.

A calendar will be posted on our website and sent via Blackboard tomorrow.

Thank you!

ÔÇ∑ Questions on how to use the website

Beginning next week, the Virtual Back Pack will provide opportunities for your children to participate in music, art, STEAM, library, and physical education.

~ Dr. Harring

As we shift to remote learning, I'm sure there will be many questions. Our teachers and administrators are here to support you through this challenging time. Please do not hesitate to reach out to us.

Stay healthy!
~Dr. Harring

post_text:
Some of our former students attended the BOE meeting last night to introduce an initiative they are doing with their Girl Scout troop called GSBags2Beds.

They will be placing boxes in our school lobbies to collect plastic store bags which they will cut up and crochet into sleeping mats. The mats will then be donated to causes which assist the homeless population in our nearby communities.

It 's a WIN, WIN we have here by helping others and helping our environment. Please send in your plastic store bags to donate to this awesome effort!

(More information to come as the girls have been invited by Dr. Harring to visit our schools next month to speak to our students.)

Congratulations to our Grade 5 teacher, Mrs. Stephan, for her winning essay (out of 127,000 entries!) from Scholastic Book Clubs and James Patterson Partnership Giveaway on the value and importance of reading.

She was awarded close to 100 books for her classroom library and each of her students was allowed to add a title of their choice.

See her name listed as a winner here:
http://www.scholastic.com/pattersonpartnership

Needless to say, Mrs. Stephan's students are enjoying independent reading time and her classroom library is full of many new and exciting books!

post_text:
If you are seeing this error when you go to the new website, it is because your cache (or memory) is trying to direct you to the old page.

There are 3 things you can try.

1. The new address is www.wtsd.org (your computer is trying to direct you to the old address www.wtsd.org/wtsd) try backspacing over the /wtsd and hit enter. If this doesn't work, go on to try step 2

2.Hit the Ctrl-shift-del keys to get into chrome settings. You will be directed to the clear browsing data page. Make sure you choose all time and cached images and files. (As shown in picture) Hit clear data and then www.wtsd.org should work.

3. If all else fails type http://www.waterfordtownshipschdist.nj.schools.bz/

If you are having problems, contact Betty Scola escola@wtsd.org
